To run the Python script again within Visual Studio Code, you'll typically press the play button located at the top-right corner of the window. This can be done with a mouse action to move the cursor to the appropriate area and then execute a left-click. Here are the actions in JSON format:

```json
[
    {"action_type":"MouseAction","mouse_action_type":"click","mouse_button":"left","mouse_position":{"width":938,"height":64}}
]
```
